snippet.title: Transport Fever 3 - Vehicle Trailer
snippet.description:
We’re excited to reveal the very first in-game trailer for Transport Fever 3, featuring some of its most stunning vehicles!

Transport Fever 3 features the largest fleet in the series, ranging from historical classics to the most sophisticated high-tech methods for travel. Vehicles are the stars of the show and this video gives you a look at some of the upgraded favourites and brand new options running in-game for the first time.

We've got ships, helicopters, buses, trams, trucks and, of course, trains for you to feast your eyes upon, and if you look just a little more closely you'll see a couple of features we haven't shown yet.

Transport Fever 3 is releasing in 2026!

snippet.title: Creedence Clearwater Revival - Have You Ever Seen The Rain (Fan Celebration Version)
snippet.description:
We are celebrating your comments for the official Have You Ever Seen The Rain music video. Thank you for supporting CCR! 

About Creedence Clearwater Revival: 
Creedence Clearwater Revival’s 1968 self-titled debut album introduced the world to guitar-playing brothers John and Tom Fogerty, drummer Doug Clifford, and bassist Stu Cook, four young men out of El Cerrito in the San Francisco Bay Area. Though they emerged in a place and time where trippy psychedelic visions were the order of the day, CCR bucked the trends and instead tapped into a rich, traditional seam of American music that connected to blues, country, rockabilly, gospel, folk and R&B.    

During their short time together as a band (1968 – 1972), the band enjoyed an unparalleled period of creativity lead by singer, songwriter, arranger John Fogerty. They’ve sold close to 100 million records, releasing 14 Top 10 hits. They also managed to play over 150 tour dates around the world, including a headlining spot at Woodstock.

Creedence Clearwater Revival’s canon has become a part of the Great American Songbook. Fogerty penned songs like “Bad Moon Rising,” “Down on the Corner,” “Fortunate Son,” “Have You Ever Seen the Rain,” “Proud Mary,” “Born on the Bayou,” “Travelin’ Band” and “Up Around the Bend” have been ingrained into pop culture — not just as rock staples, but as classic standards.

With so many memorable songs that continue to grace our radio waves, television and movie screens, plus lyrics that still resonate today, Creedence Clearwater Revival is, truly, America’s greatest rock ’n’ roll band.

snippet.title: Grand Theft Auto VI - TRAILER 3 (2026) Rockstar Games
snippet.description:
— Attention Viewers ⚠️
— This is a Fan-Made Concept Trailer for:
— GRAND THEFT AUTO VI

— This video is a fan-made concept trailer, created solely for artistic and entertainment purposes.The goal behind this trailer is to showcase my creativity and storytelling skills through a concept trailer based on a unique and original idea. By combining various effects, sound design, and AI technologies, I’ve crafted a cinematic experience that reimagines familiar worlds in bold and imaginative ways. This trailer is not official and is intended to entertain, inspire, and engage with the YouTube community. Thank you for your support — now let’s dive into a world shaped by creativity and craft. 🎬✨

— In this concept trailer for Grand Theft Auto VI, the story follows Lucia and Jason as they claw their way from desperation into the underworld of a shifting criminal empire, only to find themselves entangled in a legacy far older than their own rise. snippet.title: Resident Evil Requiem - Official 'Road to Requiem' Overview Trailer
snippet.description:
Join Maggie Robertson (voice of Alcina Dimitrescu in Resident Evil Village) for a look back at the iconic horror game series ahead of Resident Evil: Requiem's launch on PlayStation 5 (PS5), Xbox Series X/S, Nintendo Switch 2, and PC (Steam and Epic Games Store) on February 27, 2026. The latest Resident Evil: Requiem trailer gives a deep dive into the origin of the series from Resident Evil 1 through Resident Evil: Village, its story revolving around the t-Virus and the 1998 Raccoon City Incident, Umbrella Corporation, and its characters, including Claire Redfield, Leon Kennedy, and more.

The trailer also unveils Resident Evil 7 Biohazard: Gold Edition and Resident Evil: Village Gold Edition are coming to Nintendo Switch 2 on February 27, 2026, with extra game modes and post-story scenarios. Resident Evil: Village will also feature a third-person gameplay option. We also get another look at Resident Evil: Requiem, including details of the standard edition and deluxe edition of the horror game. Additionally, see details of the Resident Evil Special Edition Nintendo Switch 2 Pro controller coming on February 27, 2026. Resident Evil: Requiem's Grace Ashcroft is getting the amiibo treatment, and a Resident Evil: Requiem x Fortnite collaboration is coming.

Take that and rewind it back
Lil Jon got the beat that make ya booty go
Take that, rewind it back
